This paper deals with the problem of predicting the political leaning of an image, which involves analyzing the visual content of the image as well as the associated news article. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves collecting and processing a large dataset of images and news articles, which could fall under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a two-stage method for tackling the problem, which involves training a visual classifier, suggesting that the paper could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
